FBIS4-4644 "dreas064_d_94014" FBIS-EAS-94-064 Daily Report 4 Apr 1994 South Korea North Korea Reportedly Asks China for Food Aid North Korea Reportedly Asks China for Food Aid SK0404095694 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0905 GMT 4 Apr 94 SK0404095694 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network Korean BFN [YONHAP from Beijing] [Text] North Korea has reportedly made an urgent request to China for food support in order to overcome its worst food shortage situation. A well-informed Western source on the North Korean situation said today that North Korea secretly sent Kim Chong-u, chairman of the North Korean External Economic Committee, to Beijing last week, explained to the relevant Chinese Government officials its food shortage situation, and asked China for the emergency support.
